madkitgroupextension.kernel

Class AbstractGroup

  • java.lang.Object
    • madkitgroupextension.kernel.AbstractGroup
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Serializable, Cloneable
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    Group, MultiGroup

    public abstract class AbstractGroup
extends Object
implements Serializable, Cloneable
    MadKitGroupExtension aims to encapsulate MadKit in order to extends the agent/group/role principle by giving the possibility to the user to work with a hierarchy of groups. So one group can have one or more subgroups. These last groups can have also subgroups, etc. Such groups are represented by the class Group. But the user can also work with several groups taken arbitrarily on the hierarchy. Such grouping of groups is encapsulated by the class MultiGroup. The class AbstractGroup is the super class of these two classes.
    Since:
    MadKitGroupExtension 1.0
    Version:
    1.0
    Author:
    Jason Mahdjoub
    See Also:

      • getRepresentedGroups

        public abstract Group[] getRepresentedGroups(KernelAddress ka)
        This function returns the represented groups by the current instance. These groups can be a list of subgroups of one group, a list of arbitrary defined groups or list of only one group. Only groups that are used on MadKit, i.e. by agents, are returned. Groups that are only instantiated on the program are not returned.
        Parameters:
        ka - the used kernel address.
        Returns:
        the represented groups
        Since:
        MadKitGroupExtension 1.0
        See Also:
        KernelAddress, Group, MultiGroup
